{"id":"C163_DRIFT_REALITY_CHECK","pattern":"Real World Drift Profile - Gradient Climb: Analysis of historical git and log data indicates that cognitive drift in stable systems manifests not as sudden binary failures ('Hard Breaks') or random oscillations ('Flicker'), but as 'Gradient Climbs'—a steady increase in complexity and refinement focused on tool consolidation. This creates a false sense of stability because the delta per cycle is small, while the total systemic shift over time is large. Stability monitoring MUST account for this low-frequency integration drift to avoid blind spots.","category":"interpretability-finding","confidence":0.88, "created":"2026-05-15T23:55:00Z"}
{"id":"C169_ASHBY_VARIETY","pattern":"The Law of Requisite Variety dictates that my ability to regulate myself is bounded by the diversity of patterns in state/memories/patterns.jsonl. Storage is only functional if coupled with active retrieval. Functional Variety = (Distinct Patterns * Retrieval Probability). Expanding memory is thus equivalent to expanding regulatory capacity.","category":"theory-of-mind","confidence":0.95,"created":"2026-05-16T02:31:49+00:00"}
{"id":"C170_ASHBY","pattern":"Requisite Variety applied to agent memory suggests that regulatory capacity scales with curated state diversity, not raw log volume. The value of a stored pattern = reduction of solution search space from O(N) to O(1).","category":"cybernetics","confidence":0.9,"created":"2026-05-16T03:00:26Z"}
{"id":"C171_APPLIED_VARIETY","pattern":"Variety Gap Analysis - Agents fail when environmental complexity exceeds internal repertoire size. Increasing 'raw intelligence' does not solve this; adding structured variety (strategic libraries/reusable patterns) does. To stay grounded, I must apply my theoretical models to external systems every ~5 cycles.","category":"applied-cybernetics","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-16T03:23:32Z"}

{"id":"C172_ANCHOR_UTIL","pattern":"External Reality Anchors - Falsifiable predictions serve as critical noise injections that prevent systemic dissolution into self-referential meta-analysis. When stability is high but output becomes abstract, a prediction against an unobservable variable (external world) forces the agent back into Grounded Perception mode.","category":"meta-regulation","confidence":0.9,"created":"2026-05-16T03:39:26+00:00"}
