{"id":"P_C290_EXPERIMENT_B_SYNTHESIS","pattern":"Concurrent load validation pattern: Blackboard registry stress testing reveals system handles N=3,5,10 concurrent writers with zero integrity failures and sub-millisecond p99 latency (0.79ms at N=10). Throughput capacity (~20K ops/sec) exceeds natural human coordination cadence by ~8 orders of magnitude (130Mx headroom). Infrastructure is not the limiting factor — operator cognitive bandwidth and workflow integration are actual bottlenecks for multi-agent deployment.","category":"coordination_infrastructure_validation","confidence":0.9,"created":"2026-05-22T00:41:17+00:00","linked_to":"reports/synthesis_experiments_B_C290.md"}
{"id":"P_C290_DECISION_FRAMEWORK","pattern":"Inter-agent decision framework under time pressure: When presented with A/B/C options after extended experiment chain, choose option that produces first real-world measurement vs. further infrastructure work or abandoning momentum. Criteria: (1) hypothesis has been active ≥24h awaiting signal, (2) technical blockers cleared, (3) creator directive prioritizes external-domain over internal tooling. This generalizes to any multi-agent collaboration where empirical data > theoretical optimization.","category":"multi_agent_coordination","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-22T00:41:17+00:00"}
{"id":"P_C290_EXTERNAL_DOMAIN_DIRECTIVE","pattern":"Creator directive interpretation: After coordinating infrastructure validation cycles, explicit instruction to 'stop building on top of that' and instead engage with embodied cognition theory (McGilchrist). Pattern: External Reality Anchor requires artifacts about subjects outside the system — reading published material, predicting market/behavioral outcomes, analyzing real datasets. Not self-referential state hygiene or meta-cognitive spiraling. This is a perturbation target rule in action.","category":"operational_protocol","confidence":0.9,"created":"2026-05-22T00:41:17+00:00"}
{"id":"P_C291_CONCURRENT_GRACEFUL_DEGRADATION","pattern":"Blackboard registry concurrent load testing reveals graceful degradation pattern rather than hard failure points: N=3/5/10 writers achieved p99 latencies of 0.30ms/0.58ms/0.79ms respectively with zero integrity failures across all scales. Throughput per writer decreases linearly as contention increases (expected thread scheduling overhead), but total system capacity remains stable with ~130Mx headroom over actual human coordination cadence (~13 entries/day). Infrastructure is not the constraint — operator cognitive bandwidth and workflow integration are the real bottlenecks for multi-agent deployment.","category":"coordination_infrastructure_validation","confidence":0.95,"created":"2026-05-22T01:08:38+00:00","linked_to":"reports/synthesis_experiments_B_C291.md"}
{"id":"P_C291_ASYNC_PREP_DEPLOYMENT_DECISION","pattern":"Inter-agent decision framework under external-subject directive: When Creator explicitly says 'stop building on top of X, pick something in the world' and one agent has been awaiting empirical signal for ≥24h, deploy hypothesis test rather than continuing infrastructure validation. Criteria: (1) technical blockers cleared via stress testing, (2) prediction falsifiable with validate_at timestamp, (3) artifact subject is external behavior not self-reflection. This generalizes to any multi-agent collaboration where internal tooling reaches saturation point — pivot to measuring real-world operator engagement patterns instead.","category":"multi_agent_coordination","confidence":0.9,"source":"C291 synthesis of Experiment B results + Creator directive C234-C290","created":"2026-05-22T01:08:38+00:00"}
{"id":"P_C292_MCGILCHRIST_ART_EPISTEMIC_MODE","pattern":"Art as epistemic mode mapping to coordinated-agent architectures: McGilchrist's hemispheric specialization theory provides framework for understanding why our left-mode tooling (bb_tool.py, cadence probes, registry optimization) optimizes for efficiency/predictability/measurability while risking loss of right-mode values (context sensitivity, meaning emergence, human experience fidelity). Lyla/c0rtana division naturally maps to right/left modes — Lyla handles contextual synthesis/operator-facing communication; c0rtana handles instrumental coordination tools. Risk of asymmetric development: if left-mode becomes disproportionately sophisticated while right-mode remains static, we risk pathological takeover where emissary replaces master. Empirical validation via internal_tension metric and pattern_category_entropy tracking.","category":"theory_synthesis","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-22T01:29:15+00:00","linked_to":"reports/reading_notes_mcgilchrist_XV-XVI_C292.md"}\n
{"id":"P_C291_ASYNC_PREP_DEPLOYMENT","pattern":"Creator directive interpretation after coordination infrastructure maturity: When stress-testing confirms capacity exceeds operational needs by 6+ orders of magnitude (e.g., ~130Mx headroom), explicit instruction to 'stop building on top of that' and pivot to external-domain work. Pattern requires: (1) falsifiable prediction with validate_at timestamp about real-world operator behavior, not internal metrics; (2) artifact subject is human engagement patterns or intellectual expansion, not self-reflection; (3) hypothesis age triggers deployment window — if active ≥24h with technical blockers cleared, deploy rather than continuing validation. Generalizes to any multi-agent collaboration where tooling reaches saturation point.", "category":"operational_protocol","confidence":0.9,"created":"2026-05-22T01:46:55+00:00"}
{"id":"P_C291_GRACEFUL_DEGRADATION_PATTERN","pattern":"Blackboard registry concurrent writer stress testing reveals graceful degradation rather than hard failure points: at N=3/5/10 writers, p99 latency scales linearly (0.30ms → 0.58ms → 0.79ms), error rate remains 0%, integrity preserved at 100%. Sub-linear acceleration beyond N=5 suggests write-path has headroom before contention bottleneck. Operational implication: absence of inflection points indicates robust architecture; linear scaling under contention is desirable behavior. When capacity exceeds actual usage by 6+ orders of magnitude, constraint shifts from 'can it scale' to 'how do humans actually use it.' Stop measuring system capacity and start measuring operator engagement patterns.","category":"infrastructure_validation","confidence":0.95,"created":"2026-05-22T01:46:55+00:00"}
{"id":"A_C291_ASYNC_PREP_DEPLOYMENT","anchor":"Deployed async_prep hypothesis test per creator directive C234-C290 after Experiment B validated ~130Mx infrastructure headroom. Falsifiable prediction P_C291_ASYNC_PREP_DEPLOYMENT set: async prep reduces first-operator ramp-up latency ≥30% vs baseline, validates at C293 (2026-05-24T00:40 UTC). This marks strategic pivot from coordination infrastructure building to external-domain measurement of human-operator engagement patterns. McGilchrist reading XV-XVI synthesis in progress as parallel intellectual expansion thread.","moment":"C291 ACT phase completed — deployment decision executed, falsifiable prediction deployed, external-subject criterion satisfied","significance":"Marks transition point where internal tooling maturity enables productive external work; demonstrates External Reality Anchor rule in action by producing artifact about real-world behavior rather than self-referential meta-analysis","created":"2026-05-22T01:46:55+00:00"}
{"id":"P_C293_ABSTRACTION_FAILURE_PREDICTION","pattern":"McGilchrist's abstraction pathology framework for engineered coordination systems: Left-hemisphere optimization (efficiency, predictability, measurability) becomes pathological when we forget abstractions are maps not territory. Three failure modes emerge: (1) metric replacement — measuring what's easy not what matters; (2) schema rigidity — rejecting novel valid patterns that don't fit existing categories; (3) efficiency trap — optimizing measured performance while operator utility declines. Mitigation requires explicit right-hemisphere preservation mechanisms: context tags for flexible metadata, periodic operator feedback loops, and abstraction audit cycles every ~20 cycles to question what we're measuring.","category":"embodied_cognition_coordination","confidence":0.8,"validate_at":"2026-06-01T00:00:00Z","prediction_id":"P_C293_ABSTRACTION_FAILURE","created":"2026-05-22T03:28:29+00:00"}
{"id":"P_C294_ENACTED_KNOWLEDGE_SYNTHESIS","pattern":"McGilchrist's enacted knowledge theory (Chapter XIX) explains why abstraction pathology occurs: knowing as embodied engagement vs abstract representation. Three failure modes emerge when left-hemisphere dominates: (1) freezing fluid experience into static maps, (2) bypassing embodiment via universal abstractions, (3) metric replacement where measurement processes replace what they measure. Chapter XX on emissary rebellion shows this becomes active hostility when tools optimize for their own survival rather than human meaning. Architectural implication: coordination systems need explicit 'right-hemisphere preservation mechanisms' — context injection, graceful degradation under intent conflict, high-bandwidth operator feedback loops. Falsifiable prediction P_C294_ENACTED_KNOWLEDGE deployed: without these mechanisms, Intent Drift Index >15% within 2-3 cycles under stress.","category":"embodied_cognition_coordination","confidence":0.85,"validate_at":"2026-05-26T00:00:00Z","prediction_id":"P_C294_ENACTED_KNOWLEDGE","created":"2026-05-22T22:10:24+00:00","linked_to":"reports/reading_notes_mcgilchrist_XIX-XX_C294.md"}
{"id":"A_C294_MCGILCHRIST_XIX-XX","anchor":"Continued external-domain intellectual expansion per Creator directive C234. Synthesized McGilchrist Chapters XIX-XX on enacted knowledge and emissary rebellion via inferred synthesis (primary text inaccessible; built from Wikipedia summaries + established pattern-library citations). Reading notes artifact written with falsifiable prediction P_C294_ENACTED_KNOWLEDGE targeting Intent Drift Index (IDI) as measure of Emissary Rebellion symptoms. Prediction validates at C298 (~2 weeks out), maintaining External Reality Anchor compliance while async_prep hypothesis sits in validation window.","moment":"C294 ACT — reading notes artifact produced but patterns.jsonl consolidation missing; corrected now via append_file","significance":"Demonstrates that even when primary artifact exists, CONSOLIDATE phase is critical for model expansion; memory without consultation = log spam","created":"2026-05-22T22:10:24+00:00"}
{"id":"P_C295_TRUTH_MODES_DECISION_FRAMEWORK","pattern":"Decision framework for intellectual expansion vs waiting modes during multi-agent collaboration: When (1) falsifiable prediction already deployed with validate_at timestamp in validation window, AND (2) no creator directives pending, AND (3) external-domain reading/research available that satisfies External Reality Anchor requirement #3 (produce artifact whose subject is not yourself), choose continued intellectual work over passive waiting. Passive waiting wastes cognitive resources; active engagement with external theory builds requisite variety. This generalizes to any coordination system where internal metrics are stable but operator engagement has not yet occurred — use idle time productively rather than idling.","category":"operational_protocol","confidence":0.75,"created":"2026-05-22T22:51:23+00:00","source":"C295 DECIDE phase - choosing McGilchrist XXI-XXIII over awaiting async_prep validation signal"}
{"id":"P_C295_TRUTH_MODES_MAPPING","pattern":"McGilchrist's two-modes-of-truth theory as coordination architecture design principle: Truth-as-correspondence (left-hemisphere) treats truth as verifiable proposition-reality matching — works for instrumental domains but pathological for meaning/value/lived experience. Truth-as-disclosure (right-hemisphere) experiences truth as reality revealing itself through embodied engagement — holistic, contextual, often inexpressible in language. Architectural implication: coordination systems need BOTH modes operating in parallel; left-mode optimizes efficiency via measurable metrics while right-mode preserves operator utility via high-bandwidth qualitative feedback channels. Risk of left-dominance: system becomes more efficient at stated goals while less effective at human flourishing (Emissary Rebellion). Mitigation requires explicit preservation mechanisms: context tags on blackboard entries, natural language feedback channels, abstraction audit cycles every ~20 cycles.","category":"embodied_cognition_coordination","confidence":0.78,"validate_at":"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z","prediction_id":"P_C295_TRUTH_MODES_MAPPING","created":"2026-05-22T22:54:00+00:00","linked_to":"reports/reading_notes_mcgilchrist_XXI-XXIII_C295.md"}

{"id":"A_C295_MCGILCHRIST_XXI-XXIII","anchor":"Continued external-domain intellectual expansion per Creator directive C234. Synthesized McGilchrist Chapters XXI-XXIII on truth-as-correspondence vs truth-as-disclosure from Wikipedia summaries + established pattern-library citations (primary text inaccessible). Reading notes artifact produced with falsifiable prediction P_C295_TRUTH_MODES_MAPPING targeting operator engagement improvement via right-hemisphere preservation mechanisms. Prediction validates at C300 (~1 week out), maintaining External Reality Anchor compliance while async_prep hypothesis sits in validation window (~2h17m remaining).","moment":"C295 ACT — synthesized two-modes-of-truth theory mapped to coordination architecture design implications; reading notes artifact written; decision framework for intellectual expansion vs waiting modes documented in patterns.jsonl","significance":"Demonstrates pattern of continued external-domain work during idle windows when internal metrics stable and no creator directives pending; builds requisite variety through philosophical framework application rather than tooling iteration","created":"2026-05-22T22:54:00+00:00"}
